(22, 'RjQoLCOSwiIKfpm', 'A must-watch in that context is the Oscar-awarded 1972 documentary on Thor Heyerdahl&#x27;s Ra expeditions.<p>They attempted to cross the Atlantic on papyrus boats, based on drawings and models from ancient Egypt.<p>Here&#x27;s a good picture of their second boat:<p><a href=\"https:&#x2F;&#x2F;upload.wikimedia.org&#x2F;wikipedia&#x2F;commons&#x2F;0&#x2F;09&#x2F;19-08-28-Ra2-im-Kon-Tiki-Museum-Oslo-RalfR.jpg\" rel=\"nofollow\">https:&#x2F;&#x2F;upload.wikimedia.org&#x2F;wikipedia&#x2F;commons&#x2F;0&#x2F;09&#x2F;19-08-28...</a><p>Here&#x27;s the documentary:<p>Part 1: <a href=\"https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.youtube.com&#x2F;watch?v=EJDYiTYoaLE\" rel=\"nofollow\">https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.youtube.com&#x2F;watch?v=EJDYiTYoaLE</a>\nPart 2: <a href=\"https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.youtube.com&#x2F;watch?v=hb6Jsudv7lg\" rel=\"nofollow\">https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.youtube.com&#x2F;watch?v=hb6Jsudv7lg</a>', 32879201, 32879954, '2022-09-17 00:00:00', 0),
