(45, 'bediger4000', 'Seems like the AG of Texas and the 5th Circuit are saying that some property rights don&#x27;t exist. This seems contrary to the main thrusts of US law and to the US tradition that you have freedom of speech, but that nobody else has to pay for it.<p>Beyond that, the implications to topical forums are staggering. Any Texan can be off topic anywhere? Any Texan cannot be effectively reprimanded?<p>Do newspapers get to edit or choose letters to the editor? What other traditions are now void? I&#x27;m staggered.', 32878801, 32879286, '2022-09-17 00:00:00', 0),
